MATTHEW LIEBERMAN:
OK, so hopefully you

00:38:10.078 --> 00:38:11.090
could sort of see it.

00:38:11.090 --> 00:38:13.570
If not, this is each
of the two brains

00:38:13.570 --> 00:38:15.070
at different points in time.

00:38:15.070 --> 00:38:17.860
And you can see that the
brains are more like each other

00:38:17.860 --> 00:38:21.170
than they are their own brain
at other points in time.

00:38:21.170 --> 00:38:24.670
Now, here's the same video shown
again, this time without sound.

00:38:24.670 --> 00:38:27.250
But this time, this
person on the right

00:38:27.250 --> 00:38:29.260
